title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant Sniper WW2 Vintage M91/30
postcontent: Up for sale is an original World War II era Mosin Nagant M91/30 PU Sniper rifle. Rifle was made at Izhevsk in 1943, scope also made in 1943. Scope and scope mount was force-matched tot he rifle, meaning this rifle, like many other PU snipers, was refurbished after World War II. On the side of the scope mount, the scope number is electro-penciled, and under it, the rifle's serial number. Magazine floorplate was force-matched as well with the rifle serial number. This was commonly done when the Soviets were refurbishing their weapons. Many Tokarev rifles underwent the same process as well. Comes with the rifle, scope cover, and bayonet.610 dollars is more than fair. PU snipers can sometimes exceed 1000+ dollars.All IL firearm laws apply, 24 hour wait period, valid FOID and verification process, etc.
